&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to lead some of the most exciting work in the industry, on the cutting edge of social? Want to help grow one of the fastest-growing agencies in the US? Want to represent a company whose brand is so strong that we get unsolicited clients reaching out every week?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Account Director, you’ll lead the charge for one of our largest portfolios, driving relationship and revenue growth across a diverse ecosystem of household brands.. Internally, you’ll lead our cross-functional team to deliver innovative work. You’ll juggle competing priorities, from pricing to resourcing, as you grow your revenue and profitability. Externally, you’ll lead our clients to success they dreamed of. You’ll intuit their needs and inspire them with what’s possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a savvy business leader: someone who understands an agency P&amp;amp;L and how we grow, and equally understands a client CMO’s business struggles and how they grow. We need a socially-native thinker, who understands how to use social media to drive key client outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intrigued? Read on…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location Requirements: &lt;/strong&gt;This person must be based&amp;nbsp; in the New York City area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have proven experience leading a $5-10M+ book of business, with deep knowledge and expertise in multi-social channel marketing and innovation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You lead relationships with clients from coordinator to CMO, building deep thought partnerships based on trust and care. You act as client “therapist” to elicit and articulate their unexpressed needs and big dreams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re thirsty to grow business, with existing and new clients! You understand how to identify and unlock opportunities for profitable growth in revenue &amp;amp; relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You inspire cross-functional teams with strong and thoughtful leadership, creating an ownership and accountability culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You proactively travel to meet with clients IRL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You know how to make sound business decisions and manage competing priorities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re good with the details, and know how to develop and maintain annual, quarterly and monthly revenue forecasts and projections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You know CRM systems (we use Salesforce - prior knowledge not a requirement), and know how to track and manage pipeline, revenue, contracts, invoicing, profitability and customer satisfaction to meet or exceed established goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can participate as needed for new business intake and outbound efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years experience in an account services/marketing role with at least 6 years in a management role, ideally with deep CPG experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep social media expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to develop marketing strategies, plans and programs in social media and brand marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and examples in building, managing and motivating a high performing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measurable client growth and retention track record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly developed skill in communication, polish and presence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled partner to top-level client executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facility setting and holding boundaries and leading difficult conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very high levels of flexibility and creativity for solving problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven new business or revenue generation experience (both outbound and inbound)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intense desire to excel in an entrepreneurial, collaborative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional organi

&lt;p&gt;At Movers+Shakers, our mission is to spread joy. As Account Manager, your mission is to share this joy with our clients--in every meeting, and in every campaign.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under the leadership of your Senior Account Director, you’ll be responsible for supporting the overall client satisfaction of assigned accounts, their revenue growth, profitability, and project management. You’ll use your understanding of excellence in client services and internal team collaboration to deliver disruptive creativity. And you’ll be an integral team member to execute tactical growth plans to grow the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE SPECIFICS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Manager, you’ll manage the day-to-day relationship, success and growth of our clients. Internally, you’ll contribute to our cross-functional team to deliver innovative work. You’ll juggle competing priorities, from budgets to resourcing, as you contribute to assuring agency revenue and profitability. Externally, you’ll manage our clients needs to the success they dreamed of.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for managing and delivering joy to assigned accounts with minimum accountability for revenue of $1M-3M per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply understand and intuit the client’s needs and develop strategies to meet their business objectives; support and grow projects and processes from beginning to end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with all client team members; participate in defining account plans, needs, KPI’s and translate these requests with clear briefs/direction to the internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support intake and new business growth as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and refine client presentations, strategies and concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure project alignment with internal key team members to kick off projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee client paperwork (service agreements, SOWs, invoices, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quarterly planning and review sessions with key clients/accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain annual, quarterly and monthly revenue forecasts; track and maintain growth and status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of relevant experience, including client service at a creative agency and possibly brand marketing experience at large consumer brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of social media marketing (organic and paid); experience managing social-first brand marketing campaigns is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with national and/or global client teams and partner agency teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial spirit. Thrive in uncertainty and ambiguously-defined roles. Passion for trying new things jumping off the deep end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience nurturing client relationships and account growth within existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated, eager to learn, a drive to succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communicator, skilled writer, extremely organized, professional demeanor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to contribute in both a strategic and tactical capacity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to develop and maintain good working relationships with clients and team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds respect by personal example; is respected by and works effectively with all members of the organization and external contacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intense desire to excel in an entrepreneurial, collaborative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with top-level executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate initiative; is proactive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spreads joy!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you! 🎵💃&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

