&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a culturally-obsessed, social-first Creative Director to lead bold ideas that earn attention, drive conversation, and shape what brands look and feel like online. We want self-starters, makers, tastemakers, and creative visionaries who thrive at the intersection of storytelling, internet culture, entertainment, and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for someone who deeply understands how modern brands win in social, not just by advertising, but by becoming part of culture. You’ll lead breakthrough creative across TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, emerging platforms, influencer partnerships, and more, built to travel online.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has a sharp creative point of view, strong leadership instincts, and a proven ability to develop social-first campaigns and content that people actually want to watch, share, remix, and talk about. You instinctively know what works on the internet, why it works, and how to evolve brands to stay ahead of culture instead of reacting to it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll partner closely with strategy, production, accounts, creators, and clients to build campaigns and content that break through feeds and drive real business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead creative vision and execution across social-first brand campaigns, always-on content development, influencer activations, content series, and cultural moments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop breakthrough ideas designed for platforms like TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, and emerging social channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Push brands beyond traditional advertising into culturally relevant storytelling and internet-native creativity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee concept development, copy, art direction, content execution, and creative quality across multiple accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with strategy, production, and account teams to bring ideas from pitch through launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and mentor designers, copywriters, art directors, editors, and creators to produce best-in-class social work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create high-performing campaigns and content that balance brand storytelling with platform-native execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch prospective and existing clients on campaign concepts, creative opportunities, and cultural trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay relentlessly tapped into internet culture, trends, creators, entertainment, music, sports, fashion, and emerging digital behaviours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new formats, technologies, and creative opportunities that keep our clients ahead of the curve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with leadership on agency growth initiatives, new business pitches, and evolving creative capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10–15+ years of experience in creative advertising, brand marketing, or social-first agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong portfolio showcasing breakthrough social campaigns and culturally relevant brand storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with the Adobe Creative Cloud suite of tools alongside a foundational background in graphic design and art direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the Content Creator culture within the UK and the integration of AI tools in the creative process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven capability to translate brand objectives into reactive social content, demonstrating strong instincts for platform-native storytelling and content formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep immersion and understanding of UK culture, entertainment, and digital trends with an instinct for what drives online conversation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading campaigns from concept through production and activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Business Development (Outbound Partnerships), you are the front line of growth for Movers+Shakers, one of the pioneers in social-first creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your focus is outward, opening doors for the agency: identifying new opportunities, creating relationships with prospective clients, and bringing warm, qualified leads to our team to pursue and close. You thrive out in the world, meeting prospects, attending events, nurturing connections. You’ll represent the M+S brand with confidence and authenticity - part marketing therapist, part social evangelist, part dealmaker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports directly to the CEO/Co-Founder, who is very involved in our new business function and consultative selling process. You’ll collaborate closely with our Director of New Business, who focuses on inbound leads, including developing proposals for the prospects you bring in. You’ll also work closely with our parent company Stagwell’s new business team, as they are great partners in opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NEW BUSINESS APPROACH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our agency’s breakthrough work and strong marketing mean that our inbox is always full of inbound opportunities. They have fueled our growth &amp;amp; success over the past 5 years.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That said, we have extremely ambitious growth goals. This is a net new role we have added to further amplify the number of top quality client opportunities. We&#39;re at a moment in history where Fortune 500 CMOs are increasingly hungry for a social-first thought partner, and many don’t know where to go. They&#39;re not finding it from their current agency roster.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because of our position as innovators, new business at M+S means being a sort of therapist to CMOs and social media managers who are hungry to reinvent the way they connect to consumers. They look to us for inspiration and guidance. You will effortlessly build rapport with a CMO, and earn the admiration of a social media manager. We help them understand their problems more deeply than they did when they came in, and we package the solutions into proposals that our team can execute.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity Hunting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring a trusted playbook for new business in the creative agency space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively prospect and network - digitally and IRL - to identify and cultivate new brand relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent M+S at conferences, industry events, and client-side meetups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate warm introductions for our inbound new-business team to qualify and close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Farm existing and former client relationships for growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and nurture relationships with pitch consultants and holding-company partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship Building&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a trusted ambassador of the M+S brand - articulate our differentiators and values with clarity and passion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a structured cadence of outreach and follow-ups with prospects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with leadership to develop thought-leadership moments and speaking opportunities that attract inbound interest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with Marketing, Strategy, and Product to refine outbound messaging and ensure consistency of brand story.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feed insights back into internal teams about prospect needs, market trends, and competitor activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/

&lt;p&gt;As the Social Content Creator, you will work as a key player on an agile team, creating and producing engaging brand content that editorializes, commentates, and participates in real-time culture and trends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is obsessed with hands-on content creation and has a passion for innovation and new digital &amp;amp; social platforms. You have a background in creating TikToks, along with a deep understanding of production must-haves, a knack for ideation, strategic know-how, and a collaborative mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone who is organized, creative, and energized by making great work, whether that be concepting in partnership with the broader team, or picking up a phone and shooting/editing a piece of content themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This means making sure the production of that content is planned out, scheduled, and executed correctly (often by YOU!), and also that props and sets are considered. You will also have the opportunity to brief in and work with in-house editors on some projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideate &amp;amp; execute the creation of platform-native social content that&#39;s on strategy &amp;amp; responsive to trends and consumer-focused ideation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work independently and partnered with the creative team, content creators, influencers, and production partners in the development and execution of brand content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with account management, project management, strategy and creative teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly contribute to creative and strategic brainstorms to develop and create seamlessly executable, quick-turn content within timeline and budget parameters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and write creative briefs for content creators and influencers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and implementation of creative workflows, systems, and processes to improve creative output and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work simultaneously on multiple clients’ programs within tight deadlines, seeing projects through from start to finish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-8 years of content creation experience in a marketing setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience concepting, creating, editing, and posting brand content across owned social channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating original and remixed content&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Original: &lt;/strong&gt;capturing / shooting video and/or photography on mobile phones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remix: &lt;/strong&gt;working with existing footage and/or photography to create remixed assets&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortability working with in-app and external tools to create original content — e.g., filters, sounds, visual effects, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master of in-app editing across platforms (including TikTok, CapCut, and beyond) and external editing tools (Adobe Premiere, Davicini, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in hands-on content creation, handling production and creative execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to ideate &amp;amp; concept original ideas both independently and in collaboration with team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience concepting and executing original content across TikTok, Instagram (Reels, Stories, Feed), YouTube (including Shorts), and other emerging platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for delighting clients and going above &amp;amp; beyond&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keen eye for detail with the foresight to think about the bigger picture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Super organized,

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Freelance Influencer Marketing Manager to identify, recruit, and coordinate talent for our social-first campaign work (organic, paid, and always on). This is a remote Freelance opportunity that may vary in weekly hours on one or more client accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creator Sourcing &amp;amp; Talent Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-to-end creator management inclusive of identifying, recruiting and outreaching to talent, managing contract negotiations/redlines, budgets, content review and guiding influencers/creators with their deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and cultivate relationships with creators, influencers, managers, and agents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source UGC and creator talent using platforms like IMAI and your professional network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a vetted, organized creator roster across paid organic social needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Match creators to briefs based on brand, tone, platform, and content requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build positive, professional relationships with creators to support long-term collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support our internal “Movers+Creators” program which houses creators across various areas that M+S will tap into for quick turnaround programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creator Communication &amp;amp; Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all creator communication end-to-end, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outreach and onboarding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brief delivery and clarification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deadlines and deliverable expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow-ups and reminders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure creators clearly understand briefs, content requirements, and brand guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively flag risks, delays, or misalignment to internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate product samples as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliverables, Deadlines &amp;amp; Quality Control&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsive to the unpredictable 24/7 nature of social media campaign execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and manage creator deliverables, timelines, and submission requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate tracking of creator activity, deliverables, and performance data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor content to ensure assets are:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-brief&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivered on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate reshoots, corrections, missing lines, or pronunciation fixes as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure creators submit footage in the correct formats and specs for paid and organic use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contracts, Invoicing &amp;amp; Asset Tracking&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate creator contracts, usage terms, and approvals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure invoicing details are clear, accurate, and submitted on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track asset delivery status and usage rights across paid and organic channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal teams to ensure assets are stored, labeled, and accessible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
